			"seed": 2067,
			"version": 2,
			"versionNonce": 921254055,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994001790,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "Automatically called when an object is created.  Think of it as the \"birth certificate\" of an object.\n\n  Default Constructor    → Java auto-provides one if you write none.\n                           Movie m = new Movie();  → title=null, duration=0\n\n  Parameterized          → You hand data at birth.\n                           Movie m = new Movie(\"Inception\", 148);\n                           Analogy: filling in a form at birth registration.\n\n  Copy Constructor       → Clone an existing object (deep copy, not reference).\n                           Movie m2 = new Movie(m1);   // m2 is independent\n                           ⚠ Without it: Movie m2 = m1  means both point to SAME object.\n                              Change m2.title → also changes m1.title!  (aliasing bug)\n                           Python: import copy;  m2 = copy.deepcopy(m1)\n\n  Private Constructor    → Nobody outside can call new.  Used for SINGLETON.\n                           class Config {\n                               private static Config instance;\n                               private Config() {}          // blocked!\n                               public static Config get() {\n                                   if(instance==null) instance = new Config();\n                                   return instance;\n                               }\n                           }  → Only ONE Config ever exists (DB connection pool, Logger)",
			"fontSize": 13,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "Automatically called when an object is created.  Think of it as the \"birth certificate\" of an object.\n\n  Default Constructor    → Java auto-provides one if you write none.\n                           Movie m = new Movie();  → title=null, duration=0\n\n  Parameterized          → You hand data at birth.\n                           Movie m = new Movie(\"Inception\", 148);\n                           Analogy: filling in a form at birth registration.\n\n  Copy Constructor       → Clone an existing object (deep copy, not reference).\n                           Movie m2 = new Movie(m1);   // m2 is independent\n                           ⚠ Without it: Movie m2 = m1  means both point to SAME object.\n                              Change m2.title → also changes m1.title!  (aliasing bug)\n                           Python: import copy;  m2 = copy.deepcopy(m1)\n\n  Private Constructor    → Nobody outside can call new.  Used for SINGLETON.\n                           class Config {\n                               private static Config instance;\n                               private Config() {}          // blocked!\n                               public static Config get() {\n                                   if(instance==null) instance = new Config();\n                                   return instance;\n                               }\n                           }  → Only ONE Config ever exists (DB connection pool, Logger)",
			"lineHeight": 1.35,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "a9",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
