			"text": "🔒  I. Encapsulation  (Data Hiding)",
			"fontSize": 15,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "center",
			"verticalAlign": "middle",
			"containerId": "oop_02092",
			"originalText": "🔒  I. Encapsulation  (Data Hiding)",
			"lineHeight": 1.3,
			"fontWeight": 700,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "aE",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
		{
			"type": "text",
			"id": "vgmQrUVD",
			"x": 48,
			"y": 710,
			"width": 341.0635986328125,
			"height": 550.8000000000001,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 2109,
			"version": 2,
			"versionNonce": 1729136135,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994001790,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "🏧 Analogy: An ATM machine.\n   You press buttons (public interface) but you can't\n   reach inside and grab cash directly (private internals).\n   The machine validates your PIN before dispensing.\n\nDefinition: Bundle data + methods into one class;\nrestrict direct access to internal state.\n\nBAD (no encapsulation):\n  account.balance = -5000   # disaster!\n\nGOOD (encapsulated):\n  class BankAccount:\n      def __init__(self, balance):\n          self.__balance = balance   # private\n      def deposit(self, amt):\n          if amt > 0:\n              self.__balance += amt  # validated!\n      def get_balance(self):\n          return self.__balance\n\n  acc = BankAccount(1000)\n  acc.__balance = -9999    # AttributeError  ✔\n  acc.deposit(-500)        # silently ignored ✔\n  print(acc.get_balance()) # 1000\n\nJava: private int balance;\n      public void setBalance(int b) {\n          if(b >= 0) this.balance = b;\n      }\n\nBenefits:\n  ✔ Data integrity    ✔ Security\n  ✔ Change internals  without breaking callers",
			"fontSize": 12,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "🏧 Analogy: An ATM machine.\n   You press buttons (public interface) but you can't\n   reach inside and grab cash directly (private internals).\n   The machine validates your PIN before dispensing.\n\nDefinition: Bundle data + methods into one class;\nrestrict direct access to internal state.\n\nBAD (no encapsulation):\n  account.balance = -5000   # disaster!\n\nGOOD (encapsulated):\n  class BankAccount:\n      def __init__(self, balance):\n          self.__balance = balance   # private\n      def deposit(self, amt):\n          if amt > 0:\n              self.__balance += amt  # validated!\n      def get_balance(self):\n          return self.__balance\n\n  acc = BankAccount(1000)\n  acc.__balance = -9999    # AttributeError  ✔\n  acc.deposit(-500)        # silently ignored ✔\n  print(acc.get_balance()) # 1000\n\nJava: private int balance;\n      public void setBalance(int b) {\n          if(b >= 0) this.balance = b;\n      }\n\nBenefits:\n  ✔ Data integrity    ✔ Security\n  ✔ Change internals  without breaking callers",
			"lineHeight": 1.35,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "aF",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
