			"strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 2221,
			"version": 2,
			"versionNonce": 1077202695,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994001790,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "🏠 Analogy: Rooms in a house.\n   public    = front door — anyone can walk in\n   protected = family hallway — relatives allowed\n   default   = this floor only — same package\n   private   = your bedroom — only you\n\nModifier    Class  Package  Subclass  World\n──────────────────────────────────────────\npublic        ✔       ✔        ✔       ✔\nprotected     ✔       ✔        ✔       ✗\ndefault       ✔       ✔        ✗       ✗\nprivate       ✔       ✗        ✗       ✗\n\nExample (Java):\n  class Employee {\n      private   double salary;    // internal only\n      protected String dept;      // subclasses ok\n      public    String name;      // everyone ok\n  }\n  class Manager extends Employee {\n      void raise() { salary *= 1.1; }  // ✗ Error!\n      void info()  { System.out.println(dept); } // ✔\n  }\n\nPython (convention, not enforced):\n  self.name    = \"Bob\"    # public\n  self._dept   = \"Eng\"    # protected (convention)\n  self.__salary= 50000    # private (name-mangling)\n  # Access: emp._Employee__salary  (still accessible!)\n  # Real privacy needs @property + no setter.",
			"fontSize": 12,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "🏠 Analogy: Rooms in a house.\n   public    = front door — anyone can walk in\n   protected = family hallway — relatives allowed\n   default   = this floor only — same package\n   private   = your bedroom — only you\n\nModifier    Class  Package  Subclass  World\n──────────────────────────────────────────\npublic        ✔       ✔        ✔       ✔\nprotected     ✔       ✔        ✔       ✗\ndefault       ✔       ✔        ✗       ✗\nprivate       ✔       ✗        ✗       ✗\n\nExample (Java):\n  class Employee {\n      private   double salary;    // internal only\n      protected String dept;      // subclasses ok\n      public    String name;      // everyone ok\n  }\n  class Manager extends Employee {\n      void raise() { salary *= 1.1; }  // ✗ Error!\n      void info()  { System.out.println(dept); } // ✔\n  }\n\nPython (convention, not enforced):\n  self.name    = \"Bob\"    # public\n  self._dept   = \"Eng\"    # protected (convention)\n  self.__salary= 50000    # private (name-mangling)\n  # Access: emp._Employee__salary  (still accessible!)\n  # Real privacy needs @property + no setter.",
			"lineHeight": 1.35,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "aV",
