		{
			"type": "text",
			"id": "5EFHFrCq",
			"x": 780,
			"y": 1344,
			"width": 405.59954833984375,
			"height": 502.2000000000001,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 2249,
			"version": 2,
			"versionNonce": 1184102727,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994001790,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "Strength (weakest → strongest):\nDependency < Association < Aggregation < Composition < Inheritance\n\n━ Dependency  \"uses-a\"  (fleeting)\n  One class uses another only as method param / local var.\n  class Report:\n      def print(self, printer: Printer):  # Printer is temp\n          printer.print(self.data)\n  Printer is NOT stored; it vanishes after the call.\n\n━ Association  \"knows-a\"  (loose)\n  A Person owns a Car.  Each exists independently.\n  class Person:\n      def __init__(self, car): self.car = car  # ref stored\n  Person deleted → Car still lives.\n\n━ Aggregation  \"has-a\"  (weak ownership)  ◇─────\n  Team has Players.  Players can survive without Team.\n  class Team:\n      def __init__(self, players): self.players = players\n  Team disbanded → players = [player1, player2] still alive.\n\n━ Composition  \"has-a\"  (strong ownership)  ◆─────\n  House has Rooms.  Rooms CANNOT exist without House.\n  class House:\n      def __init__(self):\n          self.rooms = [Room(\"Bedroom\"), Room(\"Kitchen\")]\n  House demolished → rooms are also destroyed.\n\n━ Inheritance  \"is-a\"  (strongest)\n  class Dog(Animal) — Dog IS an Animal.",
			"fontSize": 12,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "Strength (weakest → strongest):\nDependency < Association < Aggregation < Composition < Inheritance\n\n━ Dependency  \"uses-a\"  (fleeting)\n  One class uses another only as method param / local var.\n  class Report:\n      def print(self, printer: Printer):  # Printer is temp\n          printer.print(self.data)\n  Printer is NOT stored; it vanishes after the call.\n\n━ Association  \"knows-a\"  (loose)\n  A Person owns a Car.  Each exists independently.\n  class Person:\n      def __init__(self, car): self.car = car  # ref stored\n  Person deleted → Car still lives.\n\n━ Aggregation  \"has-a\"  (weak ownership)  ◇─────\n  Team has Players.  Players can survive without Team.\n  class Team:\n      def __init__(self, players): self.players = players\n  Team disbanded → players = [player1, player2] still alive.\n\n━ Composition  \"has-a\"  (strong ownership)  ◆─────\n  House has Rooms.  Rooms CANNOT exist without House.\n  class House:\n      def __init__(self):\n          self.rooms = [Room(\"Bedroom\"), Room(\"Kitchen\")]\n  House demolished → rooms are also destroyed.\n\n━ Inheritance  \"is-a\"  (strongest)\n  class Dog(Animal) — Dog IS an Animal.",
			"lineHeight": 1.35,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "aZ",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
