			"text": "⚖️  SOLID Principles  (OOP best practices)",
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "center",
			"verticalAlign": "middle",
			"containerId": "oop_02288",
			"originalText": "⚖️  SOLID Principles  (OOP best practices)",
			"lineHeight": 1.3,
			"fontWeight": 700,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "ag",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
		{
			"type": "text",
			"id": "O1oHGhnG",
			"x": 55,
			"y": 1924,
			"width": 594.3334350585938,
			"height": 315.90000000000003,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 2305,
			"version": 2,
			"versionNonce": 464887239,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994001790,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "S  Single Responsibility — ONE class, ONE reason to change.\n     ✗ class OrderService { placeOrder(); generateInvoice(); sendEmail(); }\n     ✔ OrderService | InvoiceService | EmailService  (separated)\n\nO  Open/Closed — extend behaviour WITHOUT modifying existing code.\n     Add new Payment type by creating UPIPayment(Payment), not editing Payment class.\n\nL  Liskov Substitution — subclass must be usable wherever parent is expected.\n     If Bird has fly(), and Penguin(Bird) throws NotImplemented for fly() → VIOLATES LSP.\n     Fix: Flyable interface only for birds that actually fly.\n\nI  Interface Segregation — many small interfaces > one fat interface.\n     ✗ interface Animal { eat(); fly(); swim(); }   (a Dog can't fly!)\n     ✔ Eatable | Flyable | Swimmable  — implement only what applies.\n\nD  Dependency Inversion — depend on ABSTRACTIONS not on concretions.\n     ✗ class Notification { MySQLLogger logger = new MySQLLogger(); }\n     ✔ class Notification { Logger logger; }  // inject any logger (MySQL, File, Cloud)",
			"fontSize": 13,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "S  Single Responsibility — ONE class, ONE reason to change.\n     ✗ class OrderService { placeOrder(); generateInvoice(); sendEmail(); }\n     ✔ OrderService | InvoiceService | EmailService  (separated)\n\nO  Open/Closed — extend behaviour WITHOUT modifying existing code.\n     Add new Payment type by creating UPIPayment(Payment), not editing Payment class.\n\nL  Liskov Substitution — subclass must be usable wherever parent is expected.\n     If Bird has fly(), and Penguin(Bird) throws NotImplemented for fly() → VIOLATES LSP.\n     Fix: Flyable interface only for birds that actually fly.\n\nI  Interface Segregation — many small interfaces > one fat interface.\n     ✗ interface Animal { eat(); fly(); swim(); }   (a Dog can't fly!)\n     ✔ Eatable | Flyable | Swimmable  — implement only what applies.\n\nD  Dependency Inversion — depend on ABSTRACTIONS not on concretions.\n     ✗ class Notification { MySQLLogger logger = new MySQLLogger(); }\n     ✔ class Notification { Logger logger; }  // inject any logger (MySQL, File, Cloud)",
			"lineHeight": 1.35,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "ah",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
