			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "📝  Java vs Python OOP — Key Differences",
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "center",
			"verticalAlign": "middle",
			"containerId": "oop_02316",
			"originalText": "📝  Java vs Python OOP — Key Differences",
			"lineHeight": 1.3,
			"fontWeight": 700,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "ak",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
		{
			"type": "text",
			"id": "hmiMMWVy",
			"x": 1220,
			"y": 1924,
			"width": 768,
			"height": 340.20000000000005,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 2333,
			"version": 2,
			"versionNonce": 1774196743,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994001790,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "Feature              Java                         Python\n────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nAccess control       enforced by compiler         convention (_,__)\nMultiple inherit.    via Interfaces only          native (MRO/C3 linearisation)\nMethod overloading   yes (diff signatures)        *args / default params\nConstructor          same name as class           __init__\nsuper()              super().method()             super().__init__()\nAbstract class       abstract keyword             ABC + @abstractmethod\nInterface            interface keyword            Protocol (typing module)\nGenerics             type-erased at runtime       TypeVar, Generic[T]\nStatic method        static keyword               @staticmethod\nClass method         n/a                          @classmethod\nNull safety          NullPointerException         AttributeError / None check\nEnum                 enum keyword                 Enum class from enum module\n\nExample of Python MRO (C3 linearisation):\n  class A: def hello(self): return \"A\"\n  class B(A): def hello(self): return \"B\"\n  class C(A): def hello(self): return \"C\"\n  class D(B, C): pass\n  D().hello()  # → \"B\"  (MRO: D → B → C → A)",
			"fontSize": 12,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "Feature              Java                         Python\n────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nAccess control       enforced by compiler         convention (_,__)\nMultiple inherit.    via Interfaces only          native (MRO/C3 linearisation)\nMethod overloading   yes (diff signatures)        *args / default params\nConstructor          same name as class           __init__\nsuper()              super().method()             super().__init__()\nAbstract class       abstract keyword             ABC + @abstractmethod\nInterface            interface keyword            Protocol (typing module)\nGenerics             type-erased at runtime       TypeVar, Generic[T]\nStatic method        static keyword               @staticmethod\nClass method         n/a                          @classmethod\nNull safety          NullPointerException         AttributeError / None check\nEnum                 enum keyword                 Enum class from enum module\n\nExample of Python MRO (C3 linearisation):\n  class A: def hello(self): return \"A\"\n  class B(A): def hello(self): return \"B\"\n  class C(A): def hello(self): return \"C\"\n  class D(B, C): pass\n  D().hello()  # → \"B\"  (MRO: D → B → C → A)",
			"lineHeight": 1.35,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "al",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
