			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994003201,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "🎯  Interview Traps & Classic Questions",
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "center",
			"verticalAlign": "middle",
			"containerId": "oop_02344",
			"originalText": "🎯  Interview Traps & Classic Questions",
			"lineHeight": 1.3,
			"fontWeight": 700,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "ao",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
		{
			"type": "text",
			"id": "tqqmf5Zy",
			"x": 55,
			"y": 2344,
			"width": 999.5819091796875,
			"height": 386.1,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 2361,
			"version": 2,
			"versionNonce": 1520501319,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1775994001790,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "1. Why no multiple class inheritance in Java?\n   → Diamond problem.  class C extends A, B — if A.display() and B.display() both exist, C.display() is AMBIGUOUS.\n     Java resolves it by banning it for classes.  Use interfaces (they have no state, so no conflict).\n\n2. Abstract class vs Interface?\n   → Abstract = IS-A + can carry shared state (fields) + partial implementation.  Subclass is related family.\n     Interface = CAN-DO contract, no state, no \"is-a\" needed.  Rule: if unrelated classes share a capability (Flyable → Bird AND Drone), use Interface.\n\n3. Overloading vs Overriding?\n   → Overloading = SAME class, DIFFERENT params, resolved at COMPILE time.  Python doesn't have it natively (use *args).\n     Overriding  = SUBCLASS redefines parent method, resolved at RUNTIME by actual object type (dynamic dispatch).\n\n4. Composition over Inheritance?\n   → Inheritance creates tight coupling (fragile base class problem — parent change breaks all children).\n     Composition is flexible: class Robot { Engine e; Arm a; }  — swap Engine without touching Robot hierarchy.\n\n5. When to use private constructor?\n   → Singleton (only one instance: Config, ConnectionPool, Logger), Static utility class (all-static helpers, Math), Factory pattern.\n\n6. What is the output?\n   Animal a = new Dog();  a.speak();   // Java\n   → \"Woof!\"  (runtime polymorphism — actual type is Dog, so Dog.speak() is called, not Animal.speak())",
			"fontSize": 13,
			"fontFamily": 1,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "1. Why no multiple class inheritance in Java?\n   → Diamond problem.  class C extends A, B — if A.display() and B.display() both exist, C.display() is AMBIGUOUS.\n     Java resolves it by banning it for classes.  Use interfaces (they have no state, so no conflict).\n\n2. Abstract class vs Interface?\n   → Abstract = IS-A + can carry shared state (fields) + partial implementation.  Subclass is related family.\n     Interface = CAN-DO contract, no state, no \"is-a\" needed.  Rule: if unrelated classes share a capability (Flyable → Bird AND Drone), use Interface.\n\n3. Overloading vs Overriding?\n   → Overloading = SAME class, DIFFERENT params, resolved at COMPILE time.  Python doesn't have it natively (use *args).\n     Overriding  = SUBCLASS redefines parent method, resolved at RUNTIME by actual object type (dynamic dispatch).\n\n4. Composition over Inheritance?\n   → Inheritance creates tight coupling (fragile base class problem — parent change breaks all children).\n     Composition is flexible: class Robot { Engine e; Arm a; }  — swap Engine without touching Robot hierarchy.\n\n5. When to use private constructor?\n   → Singleton (only one instance: Config, ConnectionPool, Logger), Static utility class (all-static helpers, Math), Factory pattern.\n\n6. What is the output?\n   Animal a = new Dog();  a.speak();   // Java\n   → \"Woof!\"  (runtime polymorphism — actual type is Dog, so Dog.speak() is called, not Animal.speak())",
			"lineHeight": 1.35,
			"autoResize": true,
			"index": "ap",
			"frameId": null,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
